 provide a pairing code before the bot processes their input. It also features a live Canvas for visual work and supports companion apps for macOS and mobile operating systems. The system is designed to be highly versatile, offering voice wake capabilities and multi-agent routing for isolated tasks.","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Rating","children":[]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Overall","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Versatility: [5]","plainChildren":""},{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Security: [4]","plainChildren":""},{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Multi-device Support: [4]","plainChildren":""}]}]}],"sourcePath":"openclaw.md"},{"type":"header","level":1,"content":"OpenCode - https://opencode.ai","children":[{"type":"text","content":"OpenCode is a provider-agnostic, open-source alternative to Claude Code with a heavy focus on the terminal user interface (TUI). It is developed by the creators of terminal.shop with the intent to maximize developer productivity within terminal environments."},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"General Info","children":[]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Vendor","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Anomaly Co","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"License","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Not Disclosed","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Open Source","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Yes","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Capabilities","children":[]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Interface Type","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"CLI","plainChildren":""},{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"TUI","plainChildren":""},{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Desktop App","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Platform Support","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"MacOS","plainChildren":""},{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Linux","plainChildren":""},{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Windows","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Model Providers","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Multi-provider","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Authentication","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Not Specified In Source","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Extensibility","children":[]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"MCP Support","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"No","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Skills","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"No","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Commands","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Yes","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Hooks","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"No","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Subagents","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Yes","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Other","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"LSP","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Source","children":[]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Source File","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"opencode.md","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Description","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"OpenCode utilizes a distinct agent architecture featuring a \"build\" agent for active development and a \"plan\" agent for read-only analysis. The tool is designed with a client/server architecture, allowing the TUI to run as a remote client while the server handles core logic. It includes out-of-the-box support for Language Server Protocol (LSP) to enhance code intelligence during sessions. The project maintains a philosophy of being 100% open source and decoupled from any specific model provider.","plainChildren":""}]}]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Rating","children":[]},{"type":"header","level":2,"content":"Overall","children":[{"type":"list","level":2,"children":[{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Philosophy: [4]","plainChildren":""},{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Interface: [3]","plainChildren":""},{"type":"item","level":1,"content":"Architecture: [4]","plainChildren":""}]}]}],"sourcePath":"opencode.md"}]